& [SourceSet] is the bounded scoped-construction frame
  + [source_001] is Clay Mathematics Institute Hodge problem statement
    = link: https://www.claymath.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/hodge.pdf
    = use: keeps the formal target as rational Hodge classes being rational combinations of algebraic cycle classes
  + [source_002] is Arapura and Kang, Known cases of the Hodge conjecture
    = link: https://arxiv.org/abs/2105.04695
    = use: known-case landscape and caution that mechanism scope matters
  + [source_003] is Zucker, The Hodge conjecture for cubic fourfolds
    = link: https://www.numdam.org/article/CM_1977__34_2_199_0.pdf
    = use: cubic fourfolds are a known scoped case where codimension-two Hodge classes are algebraic
  + [source_004] is Hassett, Special cubic fourfolds
    = link: https://www.math.brown.edu/bhassett/papers/cubics/cubic.pdf
    = use: special cubic fourfolds form Noether-Lefschetz divisors where extra algebraic cycles are the defining signal
  + [source_005] is Nollet, Developments in Noether-Lefschetz Theory
    = link: https://faculty.tcu.edu/snollet/research/SURVEY1.pdf
    = use: Noether-Lefschetz theory supplies a family/traversal lens for when extra Hodge classes become algebraic cycle questions

& [ScopedTargetSelection] is the result
  + [selected_family] is cubic fourfolds and special cubic fourfold Noether-Lefschetz loci
  + [codimension] is codimension two cycles on fourfolds
  + [why_selected] is this family gives a concrete version of memory-anchor language: an extra Hodge class signals special geometry and asks for an algebraic surface/cycle
  + [known_case_boundary] is cubic fourfold Hodge conjecture is known, so this target is calibration and construction-analysis rather than general proof
  + [construction_signal] is special cubic fourfolds are organized by extra algebraic cycles and discriminant divisors in moduli
  + [symbolic_mapping] is memory anchor maps to extra Hodge class; traversal maps to Noether-Lefschetz locus in moduli; realization maps to an algebraic surface/cycle

& [BoundaryUpdate] is the adjusted Hodge state
  + [old_boundary] is construction of algebraic cycles in rational higher codimension
  + [adjusted_boundary] is scoped families such as cubic fourfolds can calibrate what successful realization looks like, but they do not provide a general construction method for arbitrary smooth projective varieties
  + [best_new_shape] is Hodge inquiry should use special cubic fourfolds as a calibration laboratory for anchor-to-cycle realization
  + [first_remaining_lock] is no transfer from special-family realization to general rational higher-codimension Hodge classes
  + [second_remaining_lock] is no algorithm taking arbitrary Hodge class input and producing algebraic cycle output
  + [proof_promotion] is blocked
    = reason: a known scoped case explains the shape of realization but does not solve the general Hodge conjecture

